reviews.text: Great good.  Pizza is phenomenal, subs are both tasty and very affordable, approximately half the cost of chain sandwich restaurant's.  Staff was friendly and the menu was decent sized for a pizzeria.
The best pizza here for take out .
Good food. Great deal on subs.

Food is great 
Service is great
Just wish they accepted debit card
Cash or checks only
They always get my food cooked just right yummy Cheese Sticks

Awesome that a place like this exists. The beyond meat burger was great. Texture similar to meat, made of pea protein, endorsed by Leonardo DiCaprio! 

Restaurant is in the mall section where all the kids clothes are. Ground floor. If you enter via canton rd to need to walk about 5 mins to another section of the mall. You cross over on level 2 around Chanel and Louis vuitton

Deceptive about their closing times. Please put your "last order" as your closing time. You're not the first Hong Kong restaurant to deceive people and to make people go all the way to your store only to find out that it's "last order".

I had ‘future hotdog’ & fries tonight.
Future hotdog is very small and taste so-so , it’s really over priced! Fries are crispy & much better than hotdog!

I wouldn't go back if I have other vegi choose around.

If healthy eating, animal free meal choices and environmentally conscious products was the question... Green Common has the answer!

A simply impeccable example of a cafe/restaurant/grocers in 2018 providing what a picture of the future could look like.

With menus based on big name vegan products such as “Impossible Meats,” “Dairya” and many others, this spot is my number one choice when visiting Hong Kong for both Eat In, Takeaway as well as Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner.

Excellent.

It strikes me as a restaurant whose main mission is to promote the vegan products they  sell at the adjacent store. Still, it is a creative restaurant that offers interesting vegan food mimicking meat dishes. I think their menu can be less dependent on the items sold at Green Common like Beyond burgers, Beyond Meat or Just Egg. The problem is, I have lost interest in going there again after sampling their dishes once,  as the sense of novelty vanished.

This was our first time and wow, super impressed! Kaylee was our waitress and she is one of those rare individuals who exude happiness. Prices were high but when you figure on the double portion size, not bad at all. A must do for those visiting Branson and a will do over and over for locals.  Ask to be seated in Kaylee's section, she is the best!

I love this place! They offer fun bibs with fun comments on them for people ordering the big buckets. They gave my date one, too, saying they didn't want her to feel left out. The crab legs that I ordered were delicious and the cooked veggies tasted amazing. I had so much food that I had plenty to eat as a midnight snack later.

I am a huge fan of crab so I like to go to Joe's Crab Shack whenever I am in the area! I always get the steam pots and I am never disappointed! You get a nice variety of crab legs, potatoes, shrimp, sausage and corn. They also have the restuarant placed right by the lake so the views are fantastic. I will definitely be back again!

The food was great. Our waitress, Breeana, was hopping busy but still had time to stop and grab any items we requested. Something huge for me, they have a gluten free menu! There were no issues with the menu request either. (Not everyone is kind when you have to request something gluten free.) My daughter absolutely loved "painting" her dessert. My other daughter even got full and had to take food home. (Something rare for a growing girl like her!) We hope to go back on our next trip to Branson.

For the price the food wasn't great, it was more along the lines of captain d's or long john silvers. The drinks were mostly just a mix without any alcohol, should have been top shelf for the size and price. Disappointed that we spent $100 for a dinner for two and could have had a similar experience at a fast food place. We even were seated at a table in a corner with baby seats blocking the view which would have been the only good thing about the place. I feel like we wasted our money and the trip to Branson for dinner.
